From: Convergence <convergence@daniel-blandford.github.io>
Subject: [PATCH] constraints: Ignore min_size for maximized Wayland windows

Chromium-based browsers set xdg_toplevel.set_min_size(500, 115) in
Wayland logical coordinates.  On phone displays where fractional
scaling produces a logical width below 500 px (e.g. 1224 / 2.57 = 476),
the maximization constraint bails out because the work area is smaller
than the client's declared minimum.  Mutter then sends
configure(500, 115) instead of the work area dimensions, so the browser
only renders a 115 px tall toolbar with no content.

The fullscreen constraint already skips the min_size check for Wayland
clients (since the client will render at whatever size the compositor
tells it).  Apply the same logic to maximization and size-limits:

 - constrain_maximization: skip the hminbad/vminbad early-return for
   Wayland clients so the window is maximized to the full work area
   regardless of declared min_size.

 - constrain_size_limits: skip min/max clamping for maximized Wayland
   clients, matching the existing fullscreen Wayland bypass.

Wayland clients treat set_min_size as a hint to the compositor, not a
hard rendering limit.  Chromium will happily render at 476x991 if the
compositor sends that configuration — it just asks for 500 as a
preference.

---
 src/core/constraints.c | 14 ++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 14 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/core/constraints.c b/src/core/constraints.c
index XXXXXXX..XXXXXXX 100644
--- a/src/core/constraints.c
+++ b/src/core/constraints.c
@@ -XXX,XX +XXX,XX @@ constrain_maximization (MetaWindow         *window,
   get_size_limits (window, &min_size, &max_size);
   hminbad = target_size.width < min_size.width && window->maximized_horizontally;
   vminbad = target_size.height < min_size.height && window->maximized_vertically;
-  if (hminbad || vminbad)
+  /* Wayland clients will render at whatever size the compositor sends;
+   * set_min_size is advisory.  Skip the bail-out so maximized windows
+   * fill the work area even when it is narrower than the declared
+   * minimum (e.g. Chromium on a phone with fractional scaling).
+   */
+  if ((hminbad || vminbad)
+#ifdef HAVE_WAYLAND
+      && window->client_type != META_WINDOW_CLIENT_TYPE_WAYLAND
+#endif
+      )
     return TRUE;

   /* Determine whether constraint is already satisfied; exit if it is */
@@ -XXX,XX +XXX,XX @@ constrain_size_limits (MetaWindow         *window,
   if (info->action_type == ACTION_MOVE)
     return TRUE;

 #ifdef HAVE_WAYLAND
-  if (window->client_type == META_WINDOW_CLIENT_TYPE_WAYLAND &&
-      meta_window_is_fullscreen (window))
+  /* Wayland clients render at whatever size the compositor configures;
+   * honour their min/max hints only when neither fullscreen nor
+   * maximized, so that the compositor can fill the screen even when
+   * the client's declared minimum exceeds the logical display size.
+   */
+  if (window->client_type == META_WINDOW_CLIENT_TYPE_WAYLAND &&
+      (meta_window_is_fullscreen (window) ||
+       meta_window_is_maximized (window)))
     return TRUE;
 #endif
